    <title>Code of practice for statistics: statement of compliance</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Official National Statistics published by the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills must follow the UK Statistics Authority’s &lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.statisticsauthority.gov.uk/assessment/code-of-practice/index.html"&gt;Code of Practice for Statistics&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;abbr title="The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills"&gt;BIS&lt;/abbr&gt; has prepared a number of documents related to compliance with the Code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a statement of compliance with the Code&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;additional statements related to the Code&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;a separate compliance statement on how it will meet the requirements of the Pre-release Access Order to Official Statistics 2008&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;a list of recipients of pre-release access to National Statistics produced by &lt;abbr title="The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills"&gt;BIS&lt;/abbr&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;a statement of administrative sources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
