    <title>BIS workforce management: October 2012</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;For workforce numbers, both payroll and non-payroll (contingent labour, including consultants) information is provided, split between full-time equivalents (FTE) and headcount, with payroll staff numbers mapped to standard Civil Service grades.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For costs, payroll paybill information is broken down into its component parts ie salaries, allowances, employers pensions contributions etc. For non-payroll costs, these are split between costs for consultancy and those of other non-payroll workers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Covers October of the financial year 2012 to 2013.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
